{"@context":"http://iiif.io/api/presentation/3/context.json","id":"https://digbmc.github.io/pta-manifests/phan/phan-15147/manifest.json","type":"Manifest","label":{"none":["PHAN-15147"]},"metadata":[{"label":{"none":["Timestamp"]},"value":{"none":["1:51:47"]}},{"label":{"none":["Film"]},"value":{"none":["Phantom Thread"]}},{"label":{"none":["Distance"]},"value":{"none":["close-up"]}},{"label":{"none":["Angle"]},"value":{"none":["low"]}},{"label":{"none":["Location"]},"value":{"none":["interior"]}},{"label":{"none":["Movement"]},"value":{"none":["fixed"]}},{"label":{"none":["Composition"]},"value":{"none":["dirty single"]}}],"summary":{"none":["Woman looks at man, her expression is hard to read"]},"thumbnail":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-15147/tiles/full/300,169/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":169,"width":300}],"homepage":[{"id":"PHAN-15147","type":"Text","format":"text/html","label":{"none":["Object homepage"]}}],"items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-15147/canvas/1","type":"Canvas","height":1080,"width":1920,"label":{"none":["PHAN-15147"]},"thumbnail":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-15147/tiles/full/300,169/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":169,"width":300}],"items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-15147/canvas/1/annopage-1","type":"AnnotationPage","items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-15147/canvas/1/annopage-1/anno-1","type":"Annotation","motivation":"painting","target":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-15147/canvas/1","body":{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-15147/tiles/full/1920,1080/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":1080,"width":1920,"service":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-15147/tiles","type":"ImageService3","profile":"http://iiif.io/api/image/3/level0.json"}]}}]}],"annotations":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-15147/canvas/1/page/p1","type":"AnnotationPage","items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-15147/canvas/1/b4bb8228-0753-4d8f-aea2-e8e51d40de2d","type":"Annotation","motivation":"commenting","body":[{"created":"2026-07-01T18:42:15.765Z","creator":"Ada ","purpose":"commenting","type":"TextualBody","format":"text/html","value":"<p>The film’s press kit provides the following information about Lesley Manville’s costumes and make-up: \"Anderson and [costume designer Mark] Bridges both had strong ideas about how Cyril should dress, settling on dark charcoal tones for her dresses so that Lesley Manville's English skin could sufficiently glow...Over the course of the movie, Manville wears a variety of tailored dresses and suits made by London tailor <a target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" class=\"Hyperlink SCXW214860686 BCX4\" href=\"https://vonnordheim.co.uk/\"><u>Thomas Von Nordheim</u></a>, who learned his craft in the House of Lachasse, the very last of the surviving London couture houses; chief designers during Lachasse's postwar heyday included Digby Morton, Michael Donéllan and the ubiquitous Hardy Amies, all of whom were subjects of Anderson and Day-Lewis' research for <em>Phantom Thread</em>\" (“About the Production,” 21).&nbsp;</p>"}],"target":{"type":"SpecificResource","source":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-15147/canvas/1","selector":{"type":"FragmentSelector","conformsTo":"http://www.w3.org/TR/media-frags/","value":"xywh=pixel:374.460340366242,46.103951035031855,739.8599223726114,1010.11519705414"}}}]}]}]}